---
title: Fragrant Indonesian Style Vegetable Curry with Courgette, Green Beans and Basmati Rice
description: They grow a lot of coconuts in Indonesia and love to cook with them. The country's food is often spicy but the heat is offset with sweetness from the coconuts and often a sour note too. We're attempting this balancing act in today's curry. The sauce bathing the veggies should be hot, sharp and sweet. Top it all off with golden toasted peanuts.
image: https://img.hellofresh.com/f_auto,fl_lossy,h_640,q_auto,w_1200/hellofresh_s3/image/yellow-thai-style-veggie-curry-2af8ed22.jpg
pdf: https://www.hellofresh.co.uk/recipecards/card/fragrant-indonesian-style-vegetable-curry-619f473f9a6c1c27d039e1c2-314a8cff.pdf
servings: 2
nutrition:
  calories: 672 kcal
  fat: 29 g
  saturated fat: 17 g
  carbohydrates: 85 g
  sugar: 13 g
  protein: 17 g
  sodium: 4 g
  serving size: 584
author: HelloFresh
source: https://www.hellofresh.co.uk/recipes/fragrant-indonesian-style-vegetable-curry-619f473f9a6c1c27d039e1c2
course: main course
time required: 35 minutes
cuisine: Indonesian
---

Halve, peel and thinly slice the @Red Onion{1}. Halve the @Bell Pepper{1} and discard the core and seeds. Chop into 2cm chunks. Trim the @Courgette{1}, then halve lengthways. Slice into 1cm wide half moons. Trim the @Green Beans{150%g} and chop in half. Zest and halve the @Lime{1/2}. Roughly chop the @Salted Peanuts{25%g}.

Pour the @Water{300%ml} for the rice into a #medium saucepan{} with a tightfitting
lid. Stir in the @Basmati Rice{150%g}, @Star Anise{1} and @salt{1/4%tsp}. Cover
with the lid and bring to the boil on medium high heat. Once boiling, turn the
heat down to its lowest setting. Leave to cook for ~{10%minutes}, then remove the
pan from the heat (still covered) and leave to the side for another
~{10%minutes} or until ready to serve (the rice will continue to cook in its own
steam).

Heat a large #frying pan{} on medium heat (no oil). Once hot, add the peanuts
and dry-fry until toasted, ~{2-3%minutes}. TIP: Watch them like a hawk as they
can burn easily. Once toasted, pop them into a #small bowl{} and set aside.

Pop the (now empty) frying pan back on medium heat with a drizzle of oil. Add
the onion and stir-fry until soft, ~{3-4%minutes}. Add the @Ginger Puree{1} and
@Yellow Thai Style Paste{1} along with a pinch of @sugar{pinch}(if you have some).
Stir-fry for ~{1%minute} more. Add the green beans, pepper and courgette, then
stir-fry until starting to soften, ~{3-4%minutes}. Stir in the @Coconut Milk{200%ml},
@Water{75%ml} for the sauce and @Vegetable Stock Paste{10}. Reduce the heat and
simmer until the curry has thickened and the vegetables are tender,
~{4-5%minutes}.

When the curry is cooked, stir through the @Soy Sauce{15%ml} and add a squeeze
of lime juice. Taste and add more lime juice if needed. Remove the star anise
from the rice, fluff it up with a fork then stir through the lime zest.

When everything is ready, serve the rice in #bowls{} with the Thai style veggie
curry on top. Finish by sprinkling over the toasted peanuts. Enjoy!